<ul>
  <li>python3 -m pip install ipykernel</li>
  <li>python3 -m ipykernel install -user</li>
  <li>Create a Jupyter-notebook using Python3</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="knn-steps">KNN Steps</h3>
<ul>
  <li>If we want to implement a KNN algorithm from scratch. Here are the steps:</li>
  <li>Load data</li>
  <li>Check similarity, i.e. distances between eash pair of data points</li>
  <li>Find neighbors, i.e. which data point is the k-th closest neighbor</li>
  <li>Return K closest neighbors</li>
  <li>Check accuracy</li>
  <li>It is Programming time!
‚Äì <a href="https://www.quora.com/How-is-the-k-nearest-neighbor-algorithm-different-from-k-means-clustering">https://www.quora.com/How-is-the-k-nearest-neighbor-algorithm-different-from-k-means-clustering</a></li>
</ul>

